{
  "description": "Evaluation suite for the drug-discovery agent (50 questions). Each item carries a question and a rubric of automated checks. Categories: properties (deterministic facts), toxicity (behaviour + caveats), literature (grounding), graph (cross-compound/relationship), design (generative analogs — must route to the design agent and return GROUNDED, caveated SMILES, never invented ones), hallucination (must refuse / must not invent). Checks are lenient on wording and strict on what matters: which tools ran, whether required facts/caveats appear, and whether the agent invented data. Items with manual_review=true still run and report tools/latency, but their correctness should be confirmed by a human (deep grounding / cross-compound graph correctness / claim refutation are hard to score by substring) and are excluded from the automated pass rate.",
